        <br><br>During a game against the Lakers, Irving recovered the ball after nearly losing it, splitting two defenders before finishing with a left-handed layup. 
        <br></br>Irving's ability to create his own shot is not something that can be taught, according to Celtics teammate Shane Larkin. 
        <br><br>Last season, Irving shot 55 percent from the field on plays in which he took at least 10 dribbles, the best in the NBA among players with 100 such shots. 
        <br><br>When facing Irving's impressive ball-handling skills, Lakers' Brandon Ingram suggested the only answer is to foul him.
      </TextImage>
    </section>
    
    <section>
      <Heading style="md:text-center" level="3">Split, Swerve And Serve</Heading>
